{
  "texts": [
    "In malware attack monitoring, (Kou et al. 2024) proposed a malware detection scheme based on multilevel parallel graph pooling.",
    "This method combines multiple graph neural network strategies and aggregates graph representations through the GMT (Baek et al. 2102) pooling function, which improves the accuracy of malware variant detection.",
    "In smart contract vulnerability detection, (Cai et al. 2023) proposed an approach that combines sliced joint graphs with graph neural networks.",
    "This approach uses bi-directional graphs to capture contextual features and utilizes a hybrid attention pooling layer (consisting of global attention pooling and self-attention pooling) to extract graph-level representations.",
    "This approach effectively captures key features related to vulnerabilities."
  ]
}